claim.claim-text:
1. A device for coupling a signal line to a fiber optic cable, the device comprising
a main housing including a twisted pair electrical connection;
a connector receptacle movable in relation to the main housing;
a photodetector fixed in relation to the connector receptacle, the photodetector configured to convert light signals received in the connector receptacle into electrical signals; and
circuitry for transferring the electrical signals between the fiber optic cable and signal line;
wherein the connector receptacle is pivotally supported by at least one elongated slot, the elongated slot defining an elongated shape disposed along an exterior surface of the main housing through which the connector receptacle protrudes.

12. A device for coupling a signal line to a fiber optic cable, the device comprising:
a main housing including a junction of a top portion and a bottom portion defining a cavity, the main housing including an RJ-45 jack at least partially within the cavity;
a connector receptacle movable in relation to the main housing;
a photodetector fixed in relation to the connector receptacle, the photodetector configured to convert light signals received in the connector receptacle into electrical signals; and
circuitry for transferring the electrical signals from the photodetector to the signal line via the RJ-45 jack.

19. A device for coupling a signal line to a fiber optic cable, the device comprising:
a main housing including a junction of a top portion and a bottom portion defining a cavity;
a connector receptacle movable in relation to the main housing;
a photodetector fixed in relation to the connector receptacle, the photodetector configured to convert light signals received in the connector receptacle into electrical signals; and
circuitry for transferring the electrical signals between the fiber optic cable and signal line;
wherein the connector receptacle is orbitally supported by the main housing within the cavity defined by the top portion and the bottom portion.
